            . I went to the shop on the 25th of October: I met the prisoner at the door, and prevented him from going out with the dress; he dropped the parcel, and I think one of the young persons in the shop took it up, and put it on the counter; I saw another lad at the window; his attention was directed to some one in the shop - when I stopped the prisoner he cried, and said he hoped we would forgive him; I might have touched the parcel; I did not take it from him - it dropped between us; this is the parcel - I opened it at Westminster.</p>
